content.detailedDescription:
I saw a large glowing ring in the northeast sky that was brighter than the streetlights and it got brighter and brighter. you could see the darkness through the middle of the ring then brightly illuminated spheres stared coming through the dark area out of the center.
looked like a stargate or a porthole of some type.My roomate saw it too.
this was not man made. i have a background in aiation and there were no civillian,commercial,or military lights. this was something else and it was real. i saw about 12 objects appear from the center of this disk.
content.summary: Ufo stargate illuminated ring that glowing balls came out of.

content.detailedDescription: My husband, son and i were driving home up the street by our house in huntington hills and we saw a large non blinking orange sphere flying towards us at a relatively low altitude...Maybe like a small plane. my husband at first thought it might be a helicopter with one of those big lights flying low. but it could not have been a plane or a helicopter. it made no noise at all, had no blinking lights, and flew smoothly through the sky right over our heads. we then followed it in the car up the street. it then appeared to gain speed and gain altitude. we watched it as it got smaller and smaller and started to just look like a star once it got high enough in the sky...Then it disappeared. it appeared to accelerate into space until it disappeared. this was very very strange. cant explain at all  what it could have been. we all were freaked out, when we got home my husband called the police but they said nobody had called about it. i got on line to see how to make a report.
content.summary: Large silent orange ball  flies low and then disappears into space.

content.detailedDescription:
Last night i went on my usual walk with the dog around the race course and noticed a small man standing about 200 meters away from me. i didn't take notice at first , but then as i got closer he started to wave. i walked up to the 5foot man and started talking about the weather , he then asked me if i had seen any shooting stars in the night sky tonight. i looked at him puzzlingly and he started laughing as though it was an inside joke. i told him that i regularly see them on my nightly walks. as i threw the ball for my dog to fetch i noticed a shiny blue/silver object over the other side of the lake , possible a craft?
shortly after noticing the craft , the small 5 foot man , who looked just as human as you and me , threw the ball for my dog. i kid you not the ball went about 500 meters and my dog bolted off after it. i looked at this small man with shock and said to him "dam , you've got a good arm mate" . he laughed and said thanks. we talked a little about dogs and then the strangest thing happened. a thick layer of fog started to engulfed us making it impossible to see where my dog was (specially because hes dark black) and the craft like object was covered by fog aswell. at the thought of losing my dog i ran in to the fog looking for him yelling his name. "max! max!". after a few minutes he came wagging his tale and i was relieved. i turned to walk in the direction of the 5 foot man but couldn't find him. i searched around for about 5 minutes wondering where he could of went , because he could not have gone far. i walked over to where the craft like object had been and noticed it was gone , but where it had been was folded/crushed grass. it dawned on me that this guy and his craft might have been extraterrestrial ...

i didn't think much of it at the time , but thinking back now i cant believe how stupid i was not to put the pieces together.

what was he doing by himself in the middle of a racecourse? what was this silvery object sitting on the other side of the lake.. 

it was as if this man created this fog to lose me or something .. :/
content.summary: Racecourse et encounter.

content.detailedDescription:
I just drove home from work. when i got out of my car i looked up at the night sky. i always see stars and bright objects so i started to get in the habit of looking up before i enter my home. take note that i never saw anything before that i would consider a ufo. anyways, i looked up a couple of times as i walked to my home. i then noticed a bright object far up in the sky, too far to tell the shape of it, which shot across the night sky going in a direction away from me. it had a long bright exhaust that seemed to blast out and disappear as fast as the object was visible. it lasted about one second. in fact, if it weren't for the bright exhaust i probably wouldn't have noticed it. the exhaust didn't gradually stretch out or gradually disappear. it was like a quick lightning flash behind this object. when the object left, the exhaust left, which was only one second. 

don't believe it to be a shooting star because it didn't seem to gradually get farther away in the distance. it seemed to have shot off so fast that it disappeared from sight. and it didn't seem to be something i saw in space. looked to be in the sky but high up. it went in a straight direction, level with the ground. 

now i heard about military crafts that can fly at classified high speeds. perhaps this is a government vehicle?

well i continued to look up at the sky for a few minutes after i saw this. didn't notice anything else so i went into my home. 

as for how i felt, i was excited but disappointed that it happened so fast that i couldn't get a camera to take a picture. i would swear on a bible that what i described is true.
content.summary: Ufo blasts across sky like shooting star, with bright exhaust behind it.

content.detailedDescription: My son and i were headed to get a burger around about 8pm.  driving from gypsum to eagle.  it was dark and i all of a sudden saw something blueish green flying toward us, overhead almost horizontally but maybe at about a 150 degree angle.  it was beautiful.  i asked my son age 4 if he saw it and he said he didn't.  i think when i actually really noticed it, it almost took me to look underneath my visor area for it was directly above us. it was huge though.  i thought it was probably a meteor.  so cool.  but when i heard about the needles, california sighting on the history channel, and they discribed that sighting as turqoise, i realized what i saw looked alot like the one they saw in needles.
content.summary: Blue green oblong fireball flying to earth in about 150 angle.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home on my way back from visiting my mom.  the road i was on is very windy and surrounded by crops / fields and a few houses.  as i approached a three way stop, a flickering light caught my eye just above the tree line in front of me.  i came to a complete stop, closed my eyes in disbelief, and when i opened them there were these "stars" or dots of light that were similar to the sparks of a fire work coming up from behind the trees.  they were different sizes all relativly small in shape and seemingly close to the trees.  they formed roughly a rectangular shape and moved in formation, like a flock of birds caught in the wind or the waving of a flag.  as the front moved up and back down, the rest followed.  these "stars" shot up from behind the trees up into the air and back down.  they did a sort of back flip, soared back into the air and moved in a wave like pattern.  imagine aladin on his magic carpet riding in the sky doing flips.  that is what these "stars" did.  as they crossed the street, still suspended in the sky, they went back down to my right and kept on moving towards the south.  i turned right at the three way and attempted to follow them until they got out of sight.  the total time from when i spotted them until they disappared out of sight was maybe 20 seconds or less.  after a little further investgating, i discovered the "stars" came from a corn field.  i have yet to figure out what they were.... and unfortunately i was not able to get pictures but i will keep my eyes open!
content.summary: Blanket of moving stars.

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside of my house in the front yard and i have been seeing this object once in a while thinking,may be it was a star or meteor but when i noticed yesterday that it was moving then i relized that it was not a star or meteorite since it was moving slow like a ship of sometype.It is located above the western horizon and not always in the same place.I was able to take some photos and find them very strange maybe you can enhance them bigger as i did and see some strange shapes and colors.One picture in particular shows this disc shape object and the others show these weired strings of color.I felt very excited to see such unusual objects and when i took the photos with the flash i could swear they were flashng
back.I even tried to communicate with them telepathecally to see if they could hear me but wasnt sure if they could.Today i again saw the object and i again tried to record some pictures with my phone camcorder but something jam in my phone which i found strange since i havent had too much trouble with my phone before.I am sending you these pictures because i want to know if this is a true ufo which i feel it is and if you feel that it is something else let me know because i really dont know what else it could be.Please contact me if you have any questions and also if you know anybody in california tell them to look into the western sky and they too will see this object since it has been coming around alot.Let me know if you want anymore photos since i only can send 3 per your website.

content.detailedDescription: I used to work in a different county than where i live now, (i won't say where i worked or what county yet), but my job consisted of driving around the county all night checking on things. one night when i was stopped at one of my stopping points, i noticed these unusally brite lights in the sky, there were two of them. at first i thought nothing of it except that they were strangly brite and moved very little, if any. well, i began seeing these things every night. i noticed they would come out over a tree line at about the same time every night, (between 2:30 and 3:00 am). they would always be the same distance from me, (between 1 and 2 miles). at first, for several weeks, i couldn't tell anything about these (craft) except for their really brite lights. then one night as i was approaching the area where they always were, i came upon a four way intersection where one corner had one of those really brite street lights. well, being used to this from driving the same area every night, i knew that tipping mt hat would keep the street light out of my eyes,(as this helps to see the intersection more clearly). but when i passed through the intersection and lifted my head back up i was still being blinded by a extremly brite light. i quickly hit my breaks and pointed my search light toward the (craft),(as my job required one on my truck). when i did this, the (craft) turned its light off. there, not 100 feet from me, and no more than 30 to 40 feet high, was a flying (craft). this craft was no more than 12 to 14 feet tall, and 5 to 7 feet wide at both ends. i say, at both ends, because it was in the perfect shape of an hourglass. it just sat there a few seconds then took off paralell to the road. i took off and sped up and we stayed side by side for about a mile untill it shot across the road and met back up with the other (craft). once there, it turned its light back on. just to see what would happen i again turned my search light on the object. when i did, it would turn its light out again. every night after that they would still come out at the same time and every time i would spotlight them they would turn their lights off. as soon as i turned mine off they would turn theirs back on. this went on every night all summer long. one night i seen them take turns flying through a violent thunderstorm. one would wait motionless untill the other came out, they would flash their lights at each other like they were communicating, then the other would fly in. one would always wait on the other to come out before entering the storm. i wish now i would have contacted someone with the proper equipment to videotape these (craft), but at the time i was afraid of ridecule. not to mention i was still having a hard time believing what i had seen that one night and was still seeing every night after that. i know of one other person who seen one of these objects. it was at the 4th of july fireworks display. they said that one flew over the display and before they could tell me the shape of it, i said, let me guess, it was in the shape of an hourglass. their eyes became wider as they ask if i had seen it to. i informed them that i hadn't just then but i had been watching them every night for some time. they asked what they were and i said, you tell me. i know this story sounds to wierd to be true, but i know what i saw and would take a polygraph test for anyone at anytime to prove it. i finally decided to get this off my chest and let people believe what they may. i'm stepping forward know because i've recently been watching, ufo hunters on the history channel. they taught me that theirs alot of other people out there thats seen strange objects also, and for that i would really like to thank the gentleman. i'm planning a trip back to the sightings this summer, (as its not very far from where i live). with any luck, since they were indeed there all summer, maybe they will be back. if so, then hopefully we can prove to the world that there is something strange in our skies, especially at night. oh, before i go it might interest you to know that i do not believe in life from other planets, but there is strange (craft) out there. one last thing i would like to note. just like we've all heard before, these (craft) were completely silent. even as close as i was to the object that night, i heard nothing. not even when it accelerated away.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Close encounter of the second kind.

content.detailedDescription:
I was going to mc donalds late at night.  they close at 1100 pm and it was only 1045 but yet they were already closed.  i stopped at the stop sign at whittier blvd and chestnut street which is one street away from my home and saw a ufo in the sky.  

this is not the first time i have seen this craft.  if is the second time and i have seen it again just two nights ago.  i don't believe in ufo's.  

in person the ufo is red and has round windows with lights on in them.  just like if someone has left a lamp on with a shade pulled at home.  i dont know why it does not show up like that in pictures?  it shows up as a lighted disk shaped object.

i stopped my car and rolled down the window to get a picture with my cell phone.  i took one and it did not take off or anything.  i did.  i left to find another fast food restaurant to get something to eat.

i was not afraid.  i was not even interested to be honest.  it's just the second time i have seen this object and i cant explain it.  i have been leary to tell anyone about it for fear they would think i was crazy?

the first time i saw it, it was leaning against a tree next door.  that sounds even worse i know, but its true!  it was about three months ago and when i first moved in here.  there is a large tree next door and the craft was stopped there leaning on the tree as if using the branches to conceil it or something?  it was about the same time at night and it didn't go away until i went inside to get a camera.  when i came back it was gone.

the same craft was here two nights ago.  i went to let my cat outside at aout 315 am and i saw it in the eastern sky just sitting there.  i took a few more pictures with my home camera and my cell phone too but they look black and dont show much
content.summary: Second time i saw a ufo near my house.

content.detailedDescription:
as i was driving over stillhouse creek dam near salado,tx , a glint caught my attention. directly ahead of me about 20 to 30 degrees above the horizon i noticed several white objects moving toward me at an angle. they were grouped pretty tightly and not in any kind of formation. i started to run through what they could be, jets, birds? then it got real weird. they dissapeared and then reappeared whithin a second or two.At this point they were almost above me and i pulled over as soon as i crossed the dam.I got out and looked above me to the east.They seemed to just appear suddenly.It looked like about 7 objects white, and at times round but then angular and more elongated. as they moved they would glint in the sunlight.I was wearing polerized sunglasses and when i lifted them to look they wernt there and then when i put them back on there they were.This could have been just the glare from the sun but i thought i would mention it.They moved slowly and changed direction often and quickly, at times they just dematerialized and then reappeared again.After five minutes or so they dissapeared and i didnt see them anymore.I did notice two jets flying close together right were i had just seen the objects, they were smaller and lower than airliners, like a leer type jet maybe.Also there were two chinook helicopters in the area around the lake at the same time.I am near fort hood and seeing helicopters is common but i thought it was worth a mention.I got in my truck and headed down the road bewildered by what i had just seen.
     about one mile or so later i spotted these things again, but on the west side of the road and heading east.I followed them with my eyes until they seemed to dissapear again.As soon as i could i pulled into a church parking lot and got out. i scanned the cloudless sky for them but saw nothing.And then suddenly there they were coming toward and over me.I got a really good look at them.They seemed to change in number, some appearing and some dissapearing randomly, also they seemed to change shape and not be very defineable.Most seemed to move together in unison but some would do there own thing moving at angles and in circles.At one point they seemed to be descending rapidly and then they continued on to the northeast and just vaporized in seconds.
    i have tried to rationalize what i saw but what could just dissapear and then reappear.I feel these were not material objects, it felt like i was seeing something unreal if that makes any sense. either i am totally nuts or i saw something bizzare.If there is an explaination for these things i wish i knew.
content.summary: Multiple white objects dematerializing and rematerializing.

content.detailedDescription:
2-16-09 pulsating star-like ufo in eastern sky

while driving south on highway 75 between hwy 370 and capehart rd, i happened to glance east and noticed an unusually bright "star" sitting at the 10 o'clock position, approx. 60-70 degrees off the horizon.  i have been avid astronomy for over 25 years and know the brightest stars that occupy this area of the sky to be sirius and procyon.  i���m also fairly certain it was too early for regulus or alphard to be that high above the horizon and they aren���t as bright.  i estimate it was magnitude 0 at the peak.  the object caught my attention since i knew there shouldn���t be another star that bright in the area.  it was also changing brightness levels.  i don���t believe there were any clouds to cause the brightness fluctuations and the weather history for that date verifies this:

history for omaha offutt, ne
monday, february 16, 2009

6:55 pm	34.0 ���f 	22.5 ���f 	63%	30.06 in 	10.0 miles 	sse	8.1 mph 	- 	n/a	  	clear

the object also seemed to be in motion, but there were absolutely no navigation lights as found on normal aircraft.  there were about 3-4 other jets in the sky that all had the normal strobes and lights on them.  this object then seemed to vanish after about a minute, so i pretty much forgot about it as we were approaching our exit onto capehart rd.  as we got to the exit ramp, i noticed it had returned.  a commercial airliner was flying east in the same section of the sky and this object almost seemed to make a maneuver to avoid crossing paths with the jet, then settled into a steady glide in a west-northwest direction.  i had pulled onto the shoulder and asked my passenger melissa to take a look and she saw the exact same thing.  we were both very intrigued that it seemed under intelligent control, i.E. it didn���t simply streak and fade, or have any sort of greenish trail like a meteor.  after watching for another 30-40 seconds, the object made a banking maneuver north in a deliberate fashion and then slowly faded from view.  a very impressive event for us!
content.summary: Pulsating star-like ufo.

content.detailedDescription: Sitting on the beach at night on paradise island which now is the atlantis resort.  i was facing the bay, so i'm guessing that was west.  first noticed the object moving across the water from my ten o clock.  the reason it caught my attention was because of the speed of the object.  the lights were so close to the water that at first glance i thought it was a boat, but i had never seen a boat that size move that fast.  then i got to thinking it might be a helicopter, possibly military/drug enforcement, especially when the craft moved about 200 yards from shore.  from what i remember the craft hovered in place for about 20 minutes.  i'm pretty sure it was at least that long because like a mad man i ran to the hotels front desk asking for binoculars and tried to explain to the concierge that i wasn't crazy nor a pervert.  after running to our room to tell my parents about what i was seeing i ran back to the beach to see if it was still there.  i observed the craft for about ten more minutes, during that time it was still stationary.  i saw a greenish light emitting from underneath the craft and illuminating the ocean below.  from my vantage point it appeared as if the light from the craft was either moving up from the water or  pulling water to the craft.  i've never seen anything like this so it's hard to find the words to describe it.  once it started moving out towards the open ocean is when i knew it was an airborne craft just due to the speed it was displaying, nothing like gone in an instant, but moved out towards the horizon within a ten second range.  it's something i'll never forget but due the dark skies it's hard to know for sure if it was a helicopter.  i also remember making absolutely sure that what i was seeing was what i was seeing, because for a few minutes it kind of freaked me out.
content.summary: Three lights (red,green,blue) in triangle shape.

content.detailedDescription:
My dogs were outside in our fenced in backyard at around 6:30 and i heard them barking.  i went outside to bring them in and noticed that several other area dogs were barking as well.  it was a very clear night and i looked up at the trees and noticed that there were many lights flashing around.  after looking closer, the lights at first appeared to look like small planes.  but then i noticed that they were flying really low, so i thought they were helicopters.  then one would shoot up really high, higher than a helicopter could go.  several of them would fly close together, then shoot apart.  they were triangular in shape and had at least 3 different colored bright lights, red, white and either green or blue.  they were also silent.  they appeared to be coming from the sw direction to ne.  there is a hill that they would disappear over and that area appeared to be illuminated, although we can't see down to that valley from our house.  i had my mother come out right away, and she saw the same things.  by the time my husband came outside, they had already started to disappear.  it then seemed that there were either helicopters or several planes flying around, more than we'd normally see, but they weren't the same types of crafts as we had seen 15 minutes before.  i did call the township (radnor) to ask if there was anything going on near either the androssen farm or the highschool, and they didn't have any events noted.  i told him about what i thought i'd seen and said that i've lived in this house for 12 years and hadn't seen anything like it before.  he asked that we call back if it continued.  

when i first saw them i was amazed, not worried, just sure that it was something unique.  when my husband came out, he was trying to sign a bright spot-light we have on them, but that didn't illuminate them, it just made it harder to see them.  i'm not sure how long they were out there before i came outside, but they flew around for about 10 minutes, then just disappeared over the hill and too far away for us to see.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: 5-6 triangular objects with red, white & green lights flying at fast speeds in sporadic directions.

thank you,
sonya

content.detailedDescription: I noticed two planes flying lower in the sky than usual. the first thing that came to my mind is that planes do not fly that close together or that low. i thought it was military crafts at first because they were moving rather fast. i walked around my building and when i started to look more closly at the objects, i noticed the leading craft was no plane. the craft in the back was a plane because i saw the blinking lights that planes have on them. the craft in front was moving slightly faster. there were 3 lights i could see on it all in a row. as if there were a light on the center and each wing, none on a tail. it was odd as i watched when the craft made a fast sharp turn. i soon lost sight of it. the craziest part of this experience was that my friend who i saw minute after this recieved a call from his girlfriend who called him to say she seeing a ufo being followed. she was driving down interstate 283.

content.detailedDescription: I was on facebook, my daughter playing nintendo ds. ran out of cigarettes, needed to go to the store. went outside to start my car to warm it up, in the ssw sky i noticed right away a huge ball of light, yellowish orange in color, round, about the size of a grapefruit in the sky, but i could tell it was miles and miles away. i stared at it for about 15-20 seconds. it did not move. it was a clear night out, i saw the moon, stars, and even venus. i didn't know what to think about it, i'm naturally humorous, so i was thinking to myself maybe the nuke is coming, or finally a meteor is going to hit the earth. i didn't know. i came inside and told my daughter to get ready to go, and got on facebook again and asked people to go outside and look in the sky towards the south, but to keep in mind that i'm in minnesota, so look accordingly. people went outside and looked. my sister siobhan came back to her computer and typed that it was venus, i said no, i saw venus..It's not venus. i asked couldn't they see that huge ball of light in the sky? they all said i was paranoid and silly. i went outside to get into the car, and it was gone. how can something that huge in the sky just disappear with no trace and no witnesses other that myself? i am not crazy, nor on any medications. i saw what i saw, and that's it. i googled huge ball of light in minnesota sky, and come up with nothing. also got on the nasa site, and they had nothing to look at...No search bar. looked at other ufo sites to see if anyone had seen this...No results. so here i sit...Boggled to no end. what was that? do you know? my mom also had been searching for information, but kept coming up with ufo sightings in the world that had similar descriptions of what i saw on the same day. so i contacted you all. would love a response from you letting me know if anyone else saw this thing, and if so, has anyone figured out what it was? i have never really been a ufo person, so this is a little odd for me.
content.summary: Yellowish orangish huge ball of light. dusty/hazy outter edges.

content.detailedDescription: My sister was outside in the front of our house and txted me to come outside.When i came outside she pointed in the sky to a bright light that was moving very slowly to the right.It also had blinking light on it.After we ruled out that it was not an airplane or a star or anything of that nature i called a friend that lived about 15 mins away and told him to go outside and look at the sky to see if he saw this object in the sky.He confirmed that he did.After that my sis and i watched it for about 10  mins then i went inside to get my camera,when i came back out it was gone.
content.summary: Bright light in the sky, moving very slowly to the right. i went in to get the camera and when i came back it was gone.

content.detailedDescription: Started off i was watching tv on thursday night waiting on a show to come on at 8:00pm it was about little after 7:30pm when i heard a car come down the road sounded nice (sporty) so i went outside to see if maybe  they came back so i could what it was while i was waiting i looked into the sky above where i was standing and i noticed a extremely bright light very low in the sky maybe a few hundred yards up it's hard to judge the distance because of the hills when i looked at the light it was hard to make out my eyes could not focus it seemed to be right above me at first it resembled the moon i take random pictures on my cell of just stuff nothing special and recently of the moon so i knew the moon was in opposite sky then i thought maybe skylab or meteor or something the light was very bright and blurred it had a fog like cloud coming off the bottom the sky was clear with no clouds that night the fog was moving randomly around no solid edge i tried to shield my eyes from the glare to see if i could focus better by holding my hand up was then i could see a light coming down towards me almost like 3-d that's when i went inside to get my cell phone to try to get some proof of what i was seeing i went back to same place as before held up cell above my head an took a picture i then moved over about 15ft and took one more while i was standing there i looked at the light on my phone screen to see if it was moving any seemed to be in same place not moving so i walked back to my original spot i was standing looked up again the light seemed to be coming right for me pulsating like 3-d then i got a very bad feeling something was wrong that i should go back inside it was a scary feeling that came over me that i only get in life threatening situations emergencies an such i sat back down to watch tv started feeling very sleepy next thing i remember i woke up about 1:30am my eyes were burning as if i had flash burns from the sun my pillowcase sheet and front of my shirt were wet i removed them put some ice on my eye lids and went back to sleep i awoke at 6am to get up my eyes were normal again just slight stinging by tear ducts i don't know why i feel asleep so early was'nt sleepy was waiting on a tv show to come on at 8:00pm that made me wonder what happened that morning i looked at my pictures when i zoomed the picture in was amazed of the shape the light turned out to look like solid shape of some type of craft while looking also found a small ball of light coming from the light that when zoomed in has a image of a face of some type of rodent looking face with large eyes everyone that has seen the picture says it gives them the creeps and they are amazed this is the best that i remember that happened wasn't expecting anything unusual that night all took place pretty much like i described have the pictures on my cell phone not sure how to load them for your viewing. thanks
content.summary: Witnessed bright light in night sky few hundred yards above horizon, have awesome pictures on cell phone of event.

content.detailedDescription: Saw this thing again tonight over top the same school again but on the other end!.It did the same thing,it appeared out of no where this time about 9:15pm and looked star-like but got really bright and was stationary for about 10 minutes.It slowly moved west,and i mean slowly,and made its way past the front of my building.I looked at it through binoculars most of the time and it changed colors from half of it green and other half red when it was stationary.When it moved,it began to blink andthe lights on opposite ends would blink.1 red,1 green 2 white on the middle of each side would not blink-also yellow like.The craft looked rectangular or diamond like in shape,very drak in color.Very unusual craft.It obviously has good control over what it wants to appear to look like.My husband saw this also-he couldn't figure it out but he didn't see it with binoculars either-'cos i was so fixiated i wouldn't share.
content.summary: Saw rectangular or diamond like shaped craft, sometimes blinking & stationary over top of school again tonight. very strange.

content.detailedDescription:
Driving  up rt 16 passing through rochester on way to north conway, my wife was on the phone with her mother, also driving the car. i was in the passenger seat. when around 10 pm, we both noticed a white grey orb like sphere, come over the left side of the top of trees, and heading toward our car, and down to over our roof as if it was going to crash into us. (kind of like if someone was throwing a snow ball at us from over a hill).
my wife screamed to her mom saying "what was that!" while i was looking around to see if i could follow it. but the road was dark and trees on both sides, i dont know where it went or what it was.
it came as close to the windshield to see it really good, almost hitting it.
content.summary: Whitish ball coming over tree then over our car.

content.detailedDescription: We were driving home on route 80 and all of a sudden i looked up and there were about 8 tiny red lights in a werid cicrle and then they started moving... pretty fast. i looked up and they were gone. a coupple minutes later there they were again but this time in a ladder shape paralle to each other but now there were 9 red lights instead of 8. they were moving and as they were moving they were forming into really weird shapes that almost looked like a z or almost a k. then they were flashing for a second than stoped. i could not see they for a couple seconds but when i did there were only 8 again.. theyh started droping down but like floated down until there was one left in the sky but than i could not see it anymore and it disappered. at first i thought it was a ufo but other people thought it was a landing thing for air plains. it was very very weird.
content.shape: Boomerang,  Circle,  Flash,  Square,  Rectagular,  Other,  Unknown
